Given a functor `Œ¶ : C ‚•§ C` and a natural transformation `Œµ : ùü≠ C ‚ü∂ Œ¶`, we show that it is possible to iterate `Œµ` to the power `j : J` for any well ordered set `J`, provided suitable colimits exists in `C`.

---

- [x] depends on: #19047
- [x] depends on: #19643
